Nelson returned home and sat down on the couch taring gloomily into the distance. Stahl rushed in worried for his life. Nelson muttered that he was okay, just tired. Nelson pulled Stahl close in and they kissed. Stahl looked at him before throwing him down, making love. Afterwards, they sat and Nelson talked about being as scared as he was in his whole life. Nelson then proposed to get married, but Stahl refused saying that she loved him, but wanted it to come from his heart, not from worry. He went to pick up the mess and found a file that spooked him. He searched through multiple files and was able to figure out what [[Wilson Fisk]] was up to.{{Ref|DD307}}

====Public Forum Debate====
{{Quote|No, it's a harsh reality. There are government officials who are controlled by various criminals. What [[Wilson Fisk]] has done is take all those criminals and turn them over to the [[FBI]]. And keep all those corrupt officials for himself. He's planning to turn himself into a [[Kingpin's Federal Corruption|one-stop shop]] for bribery and protection.|Foggy Nelson to [[Blake Tower]]|Upstairs/Downstairs}}
Nelson went to [[Karen Page]] to talk to her about his plan, but she told him not to as [[Wilson Fisk]] probably already thought of it. Nelson continued saying that it is proof that Fisk broke his agreement meaning he would return to prison. Page finally agreed to work with him on it. She then revealed to Nelson that she got fired for not sharing [[Daredevil]]'s identity.

At the debate, Nelson called Page, who did not pick up. Nelson stood up, starting his debate and was immediately scolded by others. He continued on to debate [[Blake Tower]], saying he was not speaking about Fisk. He based his argument on Fisk's corruption and held up files for his case. Tower's rebuttal was that he needed evidence, but Nelson continued on. He placed down the file only to see it was gone, Page took it. He quickly ran out humiliated, but also worried because he knew Page was going to do something reckless.

He thought of things Page would do and landed on his nightmare scenario, trying to talk to Fisk. He arrived at [[Presidential Hotel]] and told the [[FBI]] that Page wanted to kill Fisk. This allowed them to get her out before Fisk killed her. They argued as they walked away as Page wanted him to lash out emotionally. However, Nelson was just fearing for her life.{{Ref|DD308}}

====Ultimatum for Nelson's Meats====
[[File:Daredevil Season 3 Official Trailer17.png|{{AltFloat}}|Nelson hugs [[Karen Page]] goodbye]]
{{Quote|Foggy, that application... if anyone looks too carefully at it..."<br>"You're going to jail."<br>"Not just me. [[Anna Nelson|Mom]] and [[Edward Nelson|Dad]] signed it, too.|[[Theo Nelson]] and Foggy Nelson|Revelations}}
{{Rewrite}}
Nelson followed [[Karen Page]] to her home where she frantically packed up to leave despite Nelson not wanting her to. She explained that she betrayed [[Matt Murdock]] by revealing to [[Wilson Fisk]] that he was Daredevil. They hugged goodbye and Nelson vowed to fix everything. He then went home to find [[Marci Stahl]] happy because Nelson's speech was caught on video and became a hit. Nelson's campaign was looking up and [[Blake Tower]] was silent.

At [[Nelson's Meats]], Foggy showed everyone the viral video and his father wanted to show [[Theo Nelson]]. Instead, Theo pulled Foggy aside, telling him to take back everything he said about Fisk. Foggy asked what happened and Theo admitted that a year ago he took a deal with [[Red Lion National Bank]] when the deli was in financial problems. They taught him how to money launder despite him not knowing what it was. Theo further explained saying that [[Felix Manning]] threatened him to have Foggy take the words back or Theo, [[Anna Nelson|Anna]], and [[Edward Nelson|Edward]] would go to jail.{{Ref|DD309}}

====Familial Pressure====
{{Quote|We didn't have any say in this, Foggy. You went and pissed off the [[Kingpin|biggest mob boss]] in the [[New York City|city]], but we're the ones paying for it. Or we will if you don't do what he says."<br>"If I read that statement to the press, Fisk wins, Theo."<br>"He's already won, Fogg. Now, do the right thing. The right thing for your family.|[[Theo Nelson]] and Foggy Nelson|Reunion (Daredevil)}}
Foggy was given a speech by [[Theo Nelson]] in order to look good for [[Wilson Fisk]]. Theo blamed Foggy because all of the financial problems were due to Fisk's vendetta for Foggy. He claimed Theo knew it was fraud, but he did not care as they were only in financial trouble because Foggy left the business. Foggy then got a call from [[Matt Murdock]].{{Ref|DD311}}

====Saving Karen Page====
[[File:BMahoneyArrestsKPage.png|{{AltFloat}}|[[Brett Mahoney]] and Nelson work together]]
{{Quote|Truth is, I'm killing time."<br>"Killing time for what? Why do you keep looking at [[Maggie Grace|her]]?"<br>"Because I need to kill a few more seconds. Okay, I'm good. Agent Nadeem, I'm here for my [[Karen Page|client]].|Foggy Nelson and [[Ray Nadeem]]|Reunion (Daredevil)}}
Nelson arrived at [[Clinton Church]] and was let through by a cop who liked his campaign. Nelson talked to [[Brett Mahoney]] and then approached [[Ray Nadeem]]. Nelson claimed that he was killing time. He then looked at [[Maggie Grace]] until she gave him the signal. He then told Nadeem he was there for his client, [[Karen Page]]. He said he was surrendering his client to the [[NYPD]]. As an accomplice to murder, she was a state issue, not federal. Nadeem let Mahoney take Page.{{Ref|DD311}}

====The Trio Reunited====
[[File:Foggy and Karen.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Nelson and [[Karen Page]] thank [[Brett Mahoney]]]]
{{Quote|Nobody's above the law. The only thing powerful enough to take down scumbags like [[Kingpin|him]] is the law."<br>"He's twisted it into something that actually protects him."<br>"Federal law, maybe, but we can build a state case that even [[Blake Tower]] can't deny, force him to take it to the grand jury.|Foggy Nelson and [[Matt Murdock]]|Reunion (Daredevil)}}
Nelson and [[Karen Page]] drove with [[Brett Mahoney]] until they got to the precinct. Mahoney then let her go. Mahoney teased Nelson for running out of [[Blake Tower]]'s speech, but Page said it was her fault. They thanked Mahoney before leaving to meet with [[Matt Murdock]]. On the roof, Nelson told Murdock that he did in fact need his help. Nelson got the the point, saying that life was hard when they thought he was dead. Murdock apologized for everything he did, arguing that he believed was for their safety. The two best friends forgave each other.
[[File:Murdock Page Nelson.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Nelson and [[Matt Murdock]] reunite]]
Murdock believed that New York City would only be in peace once [[Wilson Fisk]] was dead, but Nelson tried to reassure him that they could lock him up in the worst prison where he could not compromise anyone. Murdock believed that he would always find his way out but both Nelson and Page successfully convinced him to give the system another try. Page suggested finding another witness who had every detail of Fisk's activities and keep said witness alive long enough to testify. Nelson said it would be someone with nothing to lose, but Murdock wanted someone with everything to lose: [[Ray Nadeem]].{{Ref|DD311}}

====Representing Ray Nadeem====
{{Quote|[[Wilson Fisk|Fisk]] is threatening my family. He got them dirty, and now he's using them as leverage against me."<br>"So if you win the election and take my job, Fisk will control New York's DA?"<br>"Right. So, honestly, I'm dropping out whether you give me an hour of your time or not. But I'm asking you to anyway.|Foggy Nelson and [[Blake Tower]]|One Last Shot}}
With the help of [[Brett Mahoney]] and Nelson brought [[Ray Nadeem|Ray]] and [[Seema Nadeem]] to [[Bess Mahoney]]'s home for shelter. Ray was confused on what they were doing. [[Matt Murdock]] explained that he and Nelson were representing him as [[Nelson and Murdock]]. Nelson then found [[Blake Tower]] and made him an offer. If Tower listened to Nadeem, then Nelson would drop out of the race. Nelson further explained that if he won the election, Fisk would control the office anyways because of [[Red Lion National Bank]]. Tower then agreed.
[[File:DealWithDA.png|{{AltFloat}}|Nelson oversees [[Ray Nadeem]]'s testimony]]
Nelson brought Tower to [[Fogwell's Gym]] where Nadeem started his testimony. Afterwards, Murdock and Nelson wanted full immunity, but Tower did not take it when he heard all of the horrible things. Nelson negotiated, but Tower did not budge, so they told Tower to leave. Nadeem stopped him saying he will do the time. Nelson and Murdock talked with Nelson being happy they were working again, but Murdock said they were not at the stage of partners again. Nelson assured him they will get to that stage.
[[File:DD-BeforeTheStatement.png|{{AltFloat}}|Nelson and [[Matt Murdock|Murdock]] take [[Ray Nadeem]] to court]]
Nelson was at the court house when [[Karen Page]] approached him saying there was a shootout on the road. Murdock and Nadeem finally arrived and they got him into the room. Nelson was happy that they all worked together again. Nadeem returned having testified and all looked well. Suddenly, Murdock listened through the wall and heard that the jurors had been coerced by Fisk. Under threat, they decided not to indict him, much to everyone's displeasure.
[[File:NelsonKnockedOut.png|{{AltFloat}}|Nelson is knocked out by [[Ray Nadeem]]]]
As Nadeem threw up in the restroom, Nelson tried to assure everyone that they would not give up but Murdock seemed to have lost all faith in the law. They did it Nelson's way, now he needed to do it his way. After Murdock left, Nadeem apologized and knocked Nelson out in order to save his family. Nelson then got word that Nadeem was killed in his house. An angry Murdock walked out with intentions to kill Fisk, despite Nelson's sad pleads not to.{{Ref|DD312}}

====Nadeem's Final Confession====
[[File:BMahoneyMourningAgentNadeem.png|{{AltFloat}}|Nelson asks for [[Brett Mahoney]]'s help]]
{{Quote|The court says that a person who believes that they're dying is has less incentive to lie. Therefore, anything they say is–"<br>"You're telling me this is admissible in court?"<br>"Every damn word. It's the silver bullet to take down [[Wilson Fisk|Fisk]].|Foggy Nelson and [[Karen Page]]|A New Napkin}}
Nelson found [[Brett Mahoney]] arresting [[Felix Manning]] when he brought up [[Matt Murdock|someone]] wanting to kill [[Wilson Fisk]]. Mahoney told him that that was good, but Nelson said Mahoney had an obligation. Nelson further said that killing Fisk would mean all of the bad agents would return to the work force. Mahoney complied saying that he would give protection around the hotel, but will only send in his C team. Nelson thanked him.
[[File:NelsonTalksWithPage.png|{{AltFloat}}|Nelson talks with [[Karen Page]]]]
He returned to [[Fogwell's Gym]] where Page was still not getting over [[Ray Nadeem]]'s death. She was okay with Murdock killing Fisk, but Nelson explained that if he did, he will not forgive himself meaning only more distance between their relationship. Nelson was then called by the [[FBI]] who wanted him to come in. Page told him not to, but Nelson did not want to become a wanted fugitive.
[[File:Poindexter-FNelson-InsideOffice.png|{{AltFloat}}|Nelson and [[Benjamin Poindexter]]]]
Nelson walked in and saw [[Benjamin Poindexter]] who jokingly said won $50 because they made a bet on whether he would show. Nelson then took a picture of him and the agent, posting it to his web page so the public knew where he was. Poindexter brought him into a room where they found [[Seema Nadeem]], who claimed to be willing to have cooperation with the FBI. She called Ray a monster and wanted Nelson as her lawyer.

Nelson talked to Seema who wrote in a notebook: "they are listening" while talking bad about Ray. She then said she was cooperating to "Save Sami." She said it was "Ray's idea. In the video." Nelson circled the word "video" and Seema gave him a phone. Nelson claimed to do what he can to get them through the hardships. He returned to Page where they opened the video. The sad video was of Nadeem, claiming it to be a dying declaration. He confessed to all of his crimes in aiding and abetting. He then told his wife through the video to go to the FBI and tell them he was a monster. Then get the video to Nelson. He said he loved them before ending the video.
[[File:DD313-FBIAgentsArrested.png|{{AltFloat}}|Nelson witnesses [[Wilson Fisk]]'s arrest]]
Page said it will not hold up in court, but they could put it out on social media. Nelson actually explained that a dying declaration holds up in court and will take down Fisk. However, they had to tell Murdock before he got too far. Nelson and Page waited outside the [[Presidential Hotel]] as reports said [[Daredevil]] was attacking. Despite not getting the video, Murdock still never pulled through with the killing. Instead, he forced Fisk to go back to prison. Nelson and Page watched as Fisk was taken away in cuffs. They wondered where Murdock was. Page said he should be above them.{{Ref|DD313}}

===[[Nelson, Murdock & Page]]===
====The New Beginning====
[[File:Marci Stahl with Foggy Nelson.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Nelson talks to [[Marci Stahl]]]]
{{Quote|We go back to helping people out of a crappy office, getting paid in chickens?"<br>"I think [[Theo Nelson|Theo]] would let us work out of [[Nelson's Meats|here]], to start."<br>"At least we'd have a place to sell the chickens. So what do you think?"<br>"Why the hell not?|[[Karen Page]], Foggy Nelson and [[Matt Murdock]]|A New Napkin}}
Nelson and [[Karen Page]] were present at [[Paul Lantom]]'s funeral as [[Matt Murdock]] gave a speech and farewell to his mentor, friend, and surrogate father. Afterwards, Nelson talked with [[Marci Stahl]] and they talked about his future plans. Nelson said he did not want to be a political man anymore. He then walked over to [[Blake Tower]], who was giving an interview and formally dropped out of the race of television.
[[File:Daredevil3130.png|{{AltFloat}}|Nelson's idea]]
Everyone gathered at [[Nelson's Meats]] and Foggy got word that his parents were moving to [[Tampa]]. He then spoke to [[Theo Nelson]] and told him Tower was taking down [[Red Lion National Bank]], so all Theo needed to do was pay the loan. Theo thanked him. He then walked over to Page and Murdock at the table as they talked about [[Tammy Hattley]] flipping [[Ray Nadeem]]'s public view. Nelson asked if Murdock was sticking around and he admitted to wanting to move back into his apartment. Murdock finally called them actual friends. Nelson proclaimed he had a crazy idea and needed a new napkin. He took the pen and wrote [[Nelson, Murdock & Page]] on it just like they did years ago when he and Murdock started their business. They agreed to go back to a firm as a trio and work out of the deli, and made a toast as they drank.{{Ref|DD313}}

====Thriving Business====
{{Quote|These [[Hell's Kitchen]] nostalgia is running pretty thin with you [[Matt Murdock|guys]]. You realize that, right?"<br>"Not nostalgia. Reverence for the past... yet hope for the future.|[[Karen Page]] and Foggy Nelson|Heaven's Half Hour}}
By the 2020s, [[Karen Page]] had become a lawyer,<ref>[https://variety.com/2025/tv/news/daredevil-charlie-cox-born-again-avengers-1236319940/ ‘Daredevil’ Star Charlie Cox Teases the Dark ‘Born Again’ Revival and Potential ‘Avengers’ Crossover: ‘As Long as They’ll Have Me, I’m There’]</ref> and Nelson, Murdock & Page, as attorney at law, were primarily performing pro bono work. However, for financial reasons, they occasionally took on cases for bigger clients, which allowed them to be able to continue their pro bono business practices.{{Ref|SHAaL108}} The trio ran their business out of their own [[Nelson, Murdock & Page Law Office|storefront law office]], which Nelson was a fan of, as it kept them local and he liked the people he was representing. By [[2025]], Nelson had ended his relationship with [[Marci Stahl]].

In late [[2025]], Nelson was representing a man named [[Benny Cafaro]], who had been caught on surveillance camera stealing twenty cases of {{WPS|Château Lafite Rothschild|Lafite Rothschild}} from a bonded warehouse and then telling the [[NYPD]] that he had found the bottles on the subway. Despite this, Nelson was confident that he would get Cafaro's charges dropped. Nelson received phone calls from Cafaro that someone was pursuing him, but Nelson ignored them, believing that Cafaro was paranoid; additionally, Nelson hid this from Murdock and Page, worried that it would give Murdock another reason to suit up as Daredevil. In an attempt to protect Cafaro, Nelson allowed Cafaro to stay at his apartment.
[[File:Nelson, Murdock & Page (DDBA).jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Nelson, [[Matt Murdock|Murdock]], and [[Karen Page|Page]] leave their [[Nelson, Murdock & Page Law Office|office]]]]
One night, Nelson exited the office alongside Murdock and Page as they prepared to head to [[Josie's Bar]] to celebrate NYPD Detective [[Cherry]]'s retirement. As they locked up the office, Murdock informed Nelson that [[Becky's Diner]], a place Nelson was a fan of, had closed down and had been converted into a {{WPS|SoulCycle}}, to which Nelson jokingly remarked that Murdock was evil for telling him. Page scoffed at the two men for discussing the nostalgic past of Hell's Kitchen, and Nelson told her that he was not being nostalgic, but rather had reverence for the past and hope for the future. The three attorneys then walked to Josie's Bar.{{Ref|DDBA101}}

====[[Attack on Josie's Bar|Killed by Benjamin Poindexter]]====
[[File:Foggy Nelson with Kirsten McDuffie.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Nelson sits with [[Kirsten McDuffie]]]]
{{Quote|Matt..."<br>"Just stay here. Keep calling [[Benny Cafaro|him]]."<br>"Look, I'm sorry. I... Maybe I didn't wanna give you an excuse.|Foggy Nelson and [[Matt Murdock]]|Heaven's Half Hour}}
At [[Josie's Bar]], Nelson sat with Assistant District Attorney [[Kirsten McDuffie]], and informed her of his prior employment at [[Hogarth, Chao & Benowitz]]. McDuffie, who wished to leave the District Attorney's Office and migrate into private practice, informed Nelson that Hogarth, Chao & Benowitz was one of the firms she was considering joining, and Nelson told her that he liked her ambition. McDuffie then questioned why he worked out of a [[Nelson, Murdock & Page Law Office|storefront office]] if he liked ambition, to which Nelson responded that it felt more real and that he liked most of the people he took on as clients. McDuffie then asked him about [[Benny Cafaro]], and how he had been caught on camera, but Nelson informed McDuffie that he had a strategy that would result in Cafaro's charges being dropped. McDuffie inquired as to what Nelson's strategy was and placed a bet that he would disclose it to her later that night, which Nelson claimed would not happen. Nelson then received a phone call from Cafaro, and he excused himself to go outside and answer it.
[[File:Foggy Nelson (2025).png|{{AltFloat}}|Nelson apologizes to [[Matt Murdock]]]]
Nelson spoke with Cafaro, who told him that someone was outside and was pursuing him. Nelson told Cafaro to stay calm and that he would be headed over there to check on him. As Murdock and Page emerged and asked questions, Nelson informed them of Cafaro's predicament and that he had stashed Cafaro at his apartment after he had received threats, and added his belief that Cafaro was paranoid and was on drugs. Just then, Cafaro's screams emanated from Nelson's phone, and Murdock told Nelson to stay put while he went to go check it out. Realizing that Murdock was about to do so as Daredevil, Nelson revealed that he had kept the threats hidden from Murdock as he did not want to give Murdock another excuse to suit up. Murdock then walked away, and Nelson tried to call Cafaro once more.
[[File:Foggy is shot.png|{{AltFloat}}|Nelson is shot by [[Benjamin Poindexter]]]]
Nelson succeeded in getting into contact with Cafaro once more, although Cafaro apologized, stating that he had deceived Nelson and he had divulged Nelson's location to someone. Nelson inquired into the individual's identity, but Cafaro disconnected the call. As Nelson walked up to Page, he was shot in the lungs by [[Benjamin Poindexter]] and collapsed. Nelson remained on the floor, bleeding, while Page pulled out her gun to confront Poindexter. However, before either Page or Poindexter could shoot each other, Daredevil swung through and kicked Poindexter through the window into Josie's Bar.
[[File:Foggy dies.png|{{AltFloat}}|Nelson dies from his wound]]
As a [[Attack on Josie's Bar|battle]] raged inside Josie's Bar, Page rushed to Nelson's side and applied pressure on his wound. Nelson began wheezing and looked at Page as he struggled to breathe, while Page failed to stop the immense level of blood gushing out of his wound. As Nelson's breathing became more erratic, his heartbeat slowed. Nelson kept his eyes on Page as she struggled to help him, but his heart stopped beating and he died.{{Ref|DDBA101}}

===Legacy===
[[File:In Loving Memory - Franklin 'Foggy' Nelson.png|{{AltFloat}}|Nelson's funeral card]]
{{Quote|Foggy... He was the... kindest, purest, soul I ever met. And guys like you and me, we can work a lifetime and never measure up to his decency.|[[Matt Murdock]] to [[Frank Castle]]|Sic Semper Systema}}
Nelson received a funeral, which [[Matt Murdock]] attended. Nelson's death resulted in the dissolution of [[Nelson, Murdock & Page]], with Murdock moving out of [[Hell's Kitchen]] and forming a new law firm with [[Kirsten McDuffie]] known as [[Murdock & McDuffie]], while [[Karen Page]] moved to [[San Francisco]]. Additionally, Murdock retired as Daredevil and decided to let the law handle criminals, just as Nelson preferred.

[[2026|One year later]], [[Benjamin Poindexter]] was put on trial for the eleven murders he committed at [[Josie's Bar]], including Nelson's. During the trial, Murdock testified that true justice could not be dispensed since Nelson was dead, but that Poindexter should be punished to the full extent of the law. Poindexter was then given eleven life sentences without the possibility of parole.{{Ref|DDBA101}}

