==Trivia==
*In the comics, Foggy Nelson received his nickname from [[Matt Murdock]] because of his snoring, with Murdock describing him as "a human foghorn".

==Behind the Scenes==
*Foggy Nelson in the [[Marvel Cinematic Universe]] is the second live-action incarnation of the character, following an incarnation portrayed by [[Jon Favreau]], who also portrays [[Happy Hogan]] and directed the first two ''Iron Man'' films.
**According to [[Charlie Cox]], Favreau made a reference to his portrayal of Nelson in ''[[Spider-Man: No Way Home]]'', improvising a line "''Yeah, I’m a little foggy on how that happened.''"; however, the line did not make the final cut.<ref>[https://www.cheatsheet.com/entertainment/charlie-coxs-daredevil-and-jon-favreaus-happy-hogan-joked-about-foggy-nelson-in-deleted-spider-man-no-way-home-scene.html/ Charlie Cox’s Daredevil and Jon Favreau’s Happy Hogan Joked About Foggy Nelson in Deleted ‘Spider-Man: No Way Home’ Scene]</ref>
*The decision to kill off Foggy Nelson in ''[[Daredevil: Born Again]]'' was made during the original production of the show, although it was intended to be off-screen.<ref>[https://www.marvel.com/articles/tv-shows/daredevil-born-again-foggy-nelson-death-spoilers The 'Daredevil: Born Again' Team Breaks Down that Devastating Death]</ref> According to [[Justin Benson]], the decision to retain Nelson's death for the creative overhaul was made before he and [[Aaron Moorhead]] had signed onto the show.<ref>[https://youtu.be/qrmlrhyGwMk?feature=shared&t=768 Daredevil Born Again Cast Interview- MOST VIOLENT SERIES YET, OKOYE SERIES CANCELLED]</ref> Additionally, [[Charlie Cox]] stated that he was not convinced that the decision to kill Foggy Nelson was the right decision to make.<ref>[https://extratv.com/2025/02/24/daredevil-charlie-cox-teases-brutal-event-that-changes-matt-murdock-forever-exclusive/ ‘Daredevil’: Charlie Cox Teases 'Brutal' Event That Changes Matt Murdock Forever (Exclusive)]</ref>
*[[Jake Eavey]] and [[Bryce Burke]] were stunt doubles for [[Elden Henson]] in the role of Foggy Nelson.

